                                       skos:note "The following requirements are inferred mainly from the viewpoint of reanalysis and its near-real-time continuation as users of this ECV. Some additional considerations are also made, for which explanations are given where needed." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/crima/crima-ecv#Wind-vertical-InTheMesosphere
ecv:Wind-vertical-InTheMesosphere rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                           ecv:ecv-product ;
                                  qudt:hasUnit unit:CentiM-PER-SEC ;
                                  ecv:isProductOf ecv:Upper-airWindSpeedAndDirection ;
                                  skos:definition "3D field of the vertical component of the 3D wind vector in the mesosphere." ;
                                  skos:note "The following requirements are inferred mainly from the viewpoint of reanalysis and its near-real-time continuation as users of this ECV. Some additional considerations are also made, for which explanations are given where needed." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/crima/crima-ecv#Wind-vertical-InTheMiddleAndUpperStratosphere
ecv:Wind-vertical-InTheMiddleAndUpperStratosphere rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                           ecv:ecv-product ;
                                                  qudt:hasUnit unit:CentiM-PER-SEC ;
                                                  ecv:isProductOf ecv:Upper-airWindSpeedAndDirection ;
                                                  skos:definition "3D field of the vertical component of the 3D wind vector in the middle and upper stratosphere." ;
                                                  skos:note "The following requirements are inferred mainly from the viewpoint of reanalysis and its near-real-time continuation as users of this ECV. Some additional considerations are also made, for which explanations are given where needed." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/crima/crima-ecv#Wind-vertical-InTheUpperTroposphereAndLowerStratosphere
ecv:Wind-vertical-InTheUpperTroposphereAndLowerStratosphere rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                     ecv:ecv-product ;
                                                            qudt:hasUnit unit:CentiM-PER-SEC ;
                                                            ecv:isProductOf ecv:Upper-airWindSpeedAndDirection ;
                                                            skos:definition "3D field of the vertical component of the 3D wind vector in the UTLS." ;
                                                            skos:note "The following requirements are inferred mainly from the viewpoint of reanalysis and its near-real-time continuation as users of this ECV. Some additional considerations are also made, for which explanations are given where needed." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/crima/crima-ecv#WindDirection-nearSurface
ecv:WindDirection-nearSurface rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                       ecv:ecv-product ;
                              qudt:hasUnit unit:DEG ;
                              ecv:isProductOf ecv:SurfaceWindSpeedAndDirection ;
                              skos:definition "Direction from which wind is blowing at a known height above the surface which is to be specified in the metadata." ;
                              skos:note "The wind direction from which the wind blows, is measured in Degrees (true). The entry for an east wind is 090, that for a south wind 180 and so on clockwise. Note that zero values in both wind speed and wind direction fields indicate that there was no wind blowing at the time of observation." ,
                                        "Wind directions are normally reported as an average due to their high variability. The averaging period should be reported as metadata. Timeliness requirements are for routine applications related to climate monitoring, such as assimilation into reanalyses or the update of monitoring products. Observations that miss these timeliness requirements remain useful for some climate applications and can, for example, be used in periodic revisions to climate monitoring products." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/crima/crima-ecv#WindSpeed-nearSurface
ecv:WindSpeed-nearSurface rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                   ecv:ecv-product ;
                          qudt:hasUnit unit:M-PER-SEC ;
                          ecv:isProductOf ecv:SurfaceWindSpeedAndDirection ;
                          skos:definition "Speed of air at a known height above the surface which is to be specified in the metadata." ;
                          skos:note "Wind speeds are normally reported as an average due to their high variability. The averaging period should be reported as metadata. Observations made over the ocean are not static, being mostly recorded by mobile ships and drifting buoys (Kent et al., 2019). Requirements for marine surface observations must therefore be defined in terms of the composite accuracy and sampling of the marine observing networks to achieve comparable uncertainty thresholds at similar resolution." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/crima/crima-ecv#WindVector_nearSurface
ecv:WindVector_nearSurface rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                    ecv:ecv-product ;
                           qudt:hasUnit unit:M-PER-SEC ;
                           ecv:isProductOf ecv:SurfaceWindSpeedAndDirection ;
                           skos:definition "Horizontal wind vector, at a known height above the surface which is to be specified in the metadata." ;
                           skos:note "Wind directions are normally reported as an average due to their high variability. The averaging period should be reported as metadata." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/crima/crima-ecv#ZooplanktonBiomass
ecv:ZooplanktonBiomass rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                ecv:ecv-product ;
                       qudt:hasUnit unit:MilliGM-PER-L ;
                       ecv:isProductOf ecv:Plankton ;
                       skos:definition "Weight of zooplankton by volume." ;
                       skos:note "It can be dry weight or wet weight." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/crima/crima-ecv#ZooplanktonDiversity
ecv:ZooplanktonDiversity rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                  ecv:ecv-product ;
                         qudt:hasUnit cunit:NumberOfMolecularBiologyGroupsPerUnitVolumeOrArea ,
                                      cunit:NumberOfSpeciesPerUnitVolumeOrArea ,
                                      cunit:NumberOfTraitsPerUnitVolumeOrArea ;
                         ecv:isProductOf ecv:Plankton ;
                         skos:definition "Number of species, functional traits, molecular biology groups (Operational Taxonomic Unit/OUT, other) per unit seawater volume or unit sea surface area, or unit benthos area." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/crima/crima-ecv#pCO₂
ecv:pCO₂ rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                  ecv:ecv-product ;
         qudt:hasUnit unit:ATM ;
         ecv:isProductOf ecv:InorganicCarbon ;
         skos:definition "Surface ocean partial pressure of CO₂." ;
         skos:note "Unit: μatm (micro-ATM)." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/crima/crima-ecv#14C
<http://www.semanticweb.org/crima/crima-ecv#14C> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                          ecv:ecv-product ;
                                                 qudt:hasUnit unit:PERMILLE ;
                                                 ecv:isProductOf ecv:TransientTracers ;
                                                 skos:definition "Ratio of sample to reference value (Δ14) in the water column." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/crima/crima-ecv#TotalEstimatedFluxes–Continental
<http://www.semanticweb.org/crima/crima-ecv#TotalEstimatedFluxes–Continental> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                                       ecv:ecv-product ;
                                                                              qudt:hasUnit cunit:KiloGM-CO2-PER-M2-PER-SEC ;
                                                                              ecv:isProductOf ecv:AnthropogenicGreenhouseGasEmissions ;
                                                                              skos:definition "GHG emission gridmaps (modelled output, using proxy for the spatial distribution)." ;
                                                                              skos:note "Total estimated fluxes by coupled data assimilation/ inverse models at a continental scale. This includes both “anthropogenic” and “natural” emissions and removals." .


###  http://www.semanticweb.org/crima/crima-ecv#TotalEstimatedFluxes–National
<http://www.semanticweb.org/crima/crima-ecv#TotalEstimatedFluxes–National> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                                                    ecv:ecv-product ;
                                                                           qudt:hasUnit cunit:KiloGM-CO2-PER-M2-PER-SEC ;
                                                                           ecv:isProductOf ecv:AnthropogenicGreenhouseGasEmissions ;
                                                                           skos:definition "National estimates derived from highly resolved GHG emission gridmaps (modelled output, using proxy for the spatial distribution at fine-scale resolution)." ;
                                                                           skos:note "Total estimated fluxes by coupled data assimilation/ inverse models at a national scale. This includes both “anthropogenic” and “natural” emissions and removals." .


